               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180218-16-person135">
                  EDWARD 
                  SIMMONS
               <interp inst="t18180218-16-person135" type="surname" value="SIMMONS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180218-16-person135" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180218-16-person135" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18180218-16-viclabel89" type="occupation">bookseller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-16-victim134 t18180218-16-viclabel89"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18180218-16-crimeloc90">Barbican</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-16-crimeloc90" type="placeName" value="Barbican"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-16-crimeloc90" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-16-off87 t18180218-16-crimeloc90"></join>. On the 12th of February, between eleven and twelve o'clock in the morning, the prisoner came to the window, and looked at the books which stood on the shelf there; he came to the door, I thought he was coming in, instead of which he ran down Princes-street; I followed and gave the alarm, several persons pursued him into Bridgewater-square and Fan-street - I lost sight of him. When I got into the square he was in custody. I missed a book from the window. I am sure he is the boy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180218-16-person136">
                  MARY 
                  SIMMONS
               <interp inst="t18180218-16-person136" type="surname" value="SIMMONS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180218-16-person136" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180218-16-person136" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Edward Simmons. I saw the prisoner with the book in his hand, he came towards the door, and then ran down Princes-street. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took it up to look at-it dropped out of my hand, they called stop thief; I ran away, being afraid.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180218-16-verdict91" type="verdictDescription">
